<img class=" wp-image-1247399 aligncenter" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ebola.jpg?resize=592%2C349&#038;ssl=1" alt="Ebola: DRC to declare outbreak over in 6 days — WHO" width="592" height="349" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ebola.jpg?resize=300%2C177&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ebola.jpg?resize=768%2C454&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ebola.jpg?resize=1024%2C605&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ebola.jpg?resize=58%2C34&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ebola.jpg?resize=260%2C154&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ebola.jpg?resize=200%2C118&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ebola.jpg?resize=560%2C331&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ebola.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ebola.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 592px) 100vw, 592px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> A second positive case of Ebola virus disease has been confirmed in the health zone of Butembo, North-Kivu province, in eastern Democratic Republic of the Congo, according to health authorities. The response team said the second confirmed case is a 60-year-old farmer, who died on February 10, with an epidemiological link to the first case. Both cases died and all stayed at the same health centre. Health authorities say they have deployed a team from the provincial health ministry in the field to support response actions around these two confirmed cases. For the moment, no health personnel “is infected in the area and vaccination activities against contacts of confirmed cases begin on Thursday”, the health authorities in charge of the response further said. On Monday, local health authorities and the WHO regional office announced that more than 70 contacts linked to the new positive case of Ebola virus disease have already been identified on-site in the health zone of Butembo. According to the health authorities, the majority of contacts are family members who accompanied the two victims to the hospital centre and participated in the unsecured burials. Since the resurgence of the epidemic, the samples taken from the confirmed Ebola patients have been sent to the main laboratory of the National Institute of Biomedical Research of Kinshasa (INRB) for genome sequencing to identify the strain of Ebola and determine its link to the previous outbreak. [Xinhua/NAN] Vanguard News Nigeria The World Health Organisation (WHO) said it had taken measures to effectively respond to the recent outbreak of Ebola in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC). May 14, 2017 In "News" THE World Health Organisation, WHO, has ruled out restrictions in the Democratic Republic of Congo in the wake of the outbreak of the Ebola Virus Disease in a part of the country. May 16, 2017 In "Health" The World Health Organisation (WHO) Regional Office for Africa says no fewer than 200 contacts of recent Ebola cases have been vaccinated in Beni,  Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC). WHO had, on April 10, confirmed a new case of Ebola virus in the city of Beni after 52 days… April 21, 2020 In "Health"